    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Functional and core samples",
        "",
        "## Imports",
        "",
        "This imports are needed to run the other samples presented here"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {apply, applyMethod, objOf, constant, always, tap, pipe, compose, call, juxt, thunk, thunkify, curryN, curry, @curry, _} from \"core://functional\"",
        "import {string, getFailObject, failure, id, keys, entries, typeof} from \"system://core\"",
        "import * as F from \"core://functional\"",
        "import {Proxy} from \"system://core.proxy\"",
        "import {filter,seq,any} from \"system://itertools\""
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## tap",
        "`tap` can be used to quickly write an inspection into existing code. It passes its parameters to the given function but returns the original params.",
        "E.g. to inpsect `x` in `doSomething(x)` you can write <br>",
        "`doSomething(tap(inspector, x))` and it will pass `x` to the function `inspector`"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "function myFunc(x) { console.log(\"inside myFunc\"); x+2; }",
        "let x=42;",
        "const logInspect = tap($log); // passes params to log but returns parameters as is",
        "myFunc(x);",
        "",
        "myFunc(logInspect(x));",
        "x |> logInspect(^) |> myFunc(^); ",
        "",
        "const logInspectM = msg => tap($log(msg, ?));",
        "let inspector = logInspectM(\"will pass arg to myFunc: \");",
        "myFunc(inspector(x)); // will call myFunc(x) and log x",
        "x |> inspector(^) |> myFunc(^);"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {apply, applyMethod, objOf, constant, always, tap, pipe, compose, call, juxt, thunk, thunkify, reduce, curryN, curry, @curry, arity, mute,_} from \"core://functional\"",
        "{}",
        "const mf = mute(v=>{$log(\"param:\",v); 11}); // the actual retval is removed by mute",
        "$log(arity(mf));",
        "$log(arity(v=>v));",
        "mf(42); // has no ret"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "import {minmax, typeof} from \"system://core\"",
        "import {mapArgs} from \"system://functional\"",
        "{}",
        "$log(mapArgs(v=>10*v, 1,2,3));",
        "$log(mapArgs(v=>(:v,10*v), 1,2,3));",
        "$log(mapArgs(v=>v%2?v:(:), 1,2,3,4,5));"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
