    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## User defined symbols",
        "",
        "User defined symbol are unique tokens. They can be used as singleton values and as property keys.",
        "",
        "Symbols can be created by the Symbol function. The function accepts an optional description."
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "const s1 = Symbol(\"alma\");",
        "const s2 = Symbol(\"korte\");"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "markup",
      "language": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Displaying symbols in debug extension"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "s1,s2, [[s1,s2]]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "console.log(`${s1} ${s1 == s2 ? \"=\" : \"!\"}= ${s2}`);",
        "console.log(`_ is a symbol in functional: ${_}. Its description is \"${_.description}\"`);",
        "console.log(`${Symbol.iterator} has also description: \"${Symbol.iterator.description}\"`);",
        "",
        "let d = { a: 42, [s1]: \"hidden\", [s2]: \"hidden\"};",
        "console.log(\"keys of d: \", ...keys(d)); // won't enumerate symbols",
        "console.log(`d[${s1}] = ${d[s1]}`); // can be read"
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "language": "xsmixed",
      "source": [
        "*alma(i1, i2) {",
        "    yield @first; yield i1; yield i2; yield @last;",
        "}",
        "const iter = F.genToIter(alma, 42, 24);",
        "const i_alma = F.iterify(alma);",
        "const iter2 = i_alma(24,42);",
        "console.log(...iter);",
        "console.log(...iter);",
        "console.log(...iter2);",
        "console.log(...iter2);",
        "console.log(i_alma(88)(11));",
        "",
        "const x = () => \"alma\";",
        "function stringifyWith(f) {",
        "    curry(pipe(thunkify(f), objOf(@toString)));",
        "}",
        "const defTrans = stringifyWith(curryN(1,id));",
        "console.log(\"x\" + defTrans(\"lama\"));",
        ""
      ]
    },
